President Trump has issued three key Executive Orders to address the rising tide of crime and support law enforcement officers. These actions are in response to past failures to address rising crime throughout the country. Trump is building on his initial actions to restore public safety by securing the border and tackling disregard for the law. Attorney General Jeff Sessions is trusted to restore public safety to communities across the country. Trump has shown his commitment to law enforcement officers by thanking them for their service and discussing how to reverse rising crime. Trump is following through on his commitment to address public safety and lawlessness, as he promised during the election.